--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 Multiple packs of wolves, and tigers [of all species], sat, lay, perched around two unlit, unprepared funeral pyres. It was early morning, and they had been there since it had all started, since their duties were over and Dawn and Sartha passed on. <br>
<br>
Around the circle, in the clearing, were torches, unlit. Black, ribbons hung from around the bases, fluttering gently in the wind. <br>
<br>
At the head of each pyre, were two swords. Neither had ever been used, and a single cross hung from each one, dangling and glinting in the sun's rays. <br>
<br>
Before long, someone would come for their duties of preparing the pyre, and the bodies. Then the mourners would come, and tell of their stories, their memories of each woman. The pain would flood away, and their hearts would feel free and all would be done.<br>
<br>
Until another day..  <br>
